Happens-Before Relationship in Java:?
-------------------------------------
The happens-before relationship is a memory visibility guarantee defined by the Java Memory Model (JMM).
It ensures that writes by one thread are visible to reads by another thread in a predictable order.

If action A happens-before action B, then all effects of A are guaranteed to be visible to B.

Why It Exists
Modern CPUs and compilers reorder instructions for performance.
Without explicit guarantees, one thread may never see updates made by another thread — leading to stale reads,
race conditions, and subtle bugs.

Happens-Before Rules (JMM Guarantees)
-------------------------------------
1. Program Order Rule
Within a single thread, each action happens-before the next one.
int a = 5;   // happens-before
int b = a;   // this read


2. Monitor Lock Rule (synchronized)
An unlock of a monitor happens-before every subsequent lock of the same monitor.
synchronized(lock) { x = 10; }  // unlock happens-before
synchronized(lock) { use(x); }  // next lock — x = 10 is visible

3. Volatile Variable Rule
A write to a volatile field happens-before every subsequent read of that field.
volatile boolean ready = false;
volatile int value = 0;

// Thread A
value = 42;
ready = true;  // volatile write

// Thread B
if (ready) {         // volatile read
    use(value);      // guaranteed to see 42
}

4. Thread Start Rule
Thread.start() happens-before any action in the started thread.
int x = 100;
Thread t = new Thread(() -> System.out.println(x)); // sees x = 100
t.start(); // happens-before thread body

5. Thread Join Rule
All actions in a thread happen-before Thread.join() returns.
thread.join(); // happens-before
use(result);   // result written inside thread is visible here

6. Thread Interruption Rule
A call to interrupt() happens-before the interrupted thread detects the interruption.

7. Finalizer Rule
Object constructor completion happens-before the start of its finalize().

8. Transitivity
If A happens-before B and B happens-before C, then A happens-before C.

